  "overview_metadata": {
    "overview_number": 3,
    "overview_title": "Know It Inside Out",
    "overview_subtitle": "Area and Perimeter of Triangles and Rectangles on the Coordinate Plane",
    "overview_description": "In this lesson, students calculate the perimeter and area of rectangles and triangles on the coordinate plane. They double dimensions of figures and explain how this affects the area of the figure. Students algebraically determine the non-vertical height of a triangle as they treat each side as the base. They conclude the area of a triangle remains the same regardless of the side of the triangle considered as the base and the triangle's height determined by that base."
  },
